    "description": "Host specificity of wood inhabiting fungi is a rare occurrence in tropical ecosystems, because of the high diversity of host species, which limits distribution of the fungi. However, in low diversity tropical situations, such as mangroves in Panama, the occurrence of host specificity is much higher. The island Moorea in French Polynesia supports a lower diversity than a tropical mainland ecosystem. This study examined the occurrence of host specificity of wood inhabiting fungi in an island situation. Specificity in both host species and in size of host was found to occur",
